Key Match Events: Michael Harris II made a home run-robbing catch in the seventh inning, which was described as one of the greatest catches in history.
Zack Wheeler pitched seven innings for the Phillies, limiting the Braves to four hits and no walks with seven strikeouts.
Max Fried pitched seven solid innings for the Braves.
Post-Match Reflections: Phillies manager Rob Thomson praised Michael Harris II's catch as one of the best ever seen in the game.
Several longtime Phillies press-box observers said it was the best catch they had seen at Citizens Bank Park since it opened in 2004.
Michael Harris II ranked the catch as the best he had ever made at any level of play.
Phillies reliever Jeff Hoffman expressed astonishment at the catch, noting the athleticism required.
